        options: ["ECT is contraindicated in catatonia because seizure induction is dangerous in malnourished patients","ECT should only be considered after failing at least 3 different benzodiazepine trials","ECT has a response rate of >90% for catatonia and should be considered early, especially when lorazepam response is incomplete and medical deterioration is occurring","ECT is equally effective as continued lorazepam dose escalation, so there is no urgency to initiate it"],
